7.1 The Digital Tools We Use
The platform needs a strong, secure, and flexible set of technical tools:
Front-End (What the User Sees): We use React.js or Angular (chosen because they are reliable
and fast) and Tailwind CSS for a design that looks great and works perfectly on phones and
computers.
Back-End (Data Storage): We use Google Firestore (a type of database) because it updates
information instantly, which is key for showing mission progress and issuing badges right away.
Matching Tool: A simple, custom script (written in Python and run by Google Cloud Functions) to
match skills. In the future, we may use more advanced AI to better understand the text
descriptions of student skills.
Badge System: We will connect with a proven Digital Badge platform (like Accredible) to make
